In a small #pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water, and a pinch of
@salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low; cook until rice is
tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @Garlic{1%clove}. Trim and halve @Mini Cucumber{2} lengthwise;
slice into ½-inch-thick half-moons.

Transfer cucumbers to a #medium bowl{}; generously season with @salt{}.
Toss to coat, then let sit for ~{3-5%minutes}. Rinse cucumbers; drain and
return to bowl. (You'll finish the cucumbers in Step 3.)

Meanwhile, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with a
pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}
per side.

Remove pan from heat. Stir in @Umami Ginger Sauce{4%tablespoon},
@Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%ounce}, and @Ponzu Sauce{18%milliliters}.
Turn chicken occasionally, until sauce has thickened and chicken is coated,
~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired. Transfer
chicken to a #cutting board{}.

> Swap in pork cutlets for chicken; cook 6-8 minutes per side instead.

To bowl with drained cucumbers, add @Gochujang Sauce{1/2%ounce}, garlic, half
the @Sesame Oil{1%tablespoon}, remaining ponzu, and @Korean Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon}
to taste. Toss to coat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Thinly slice chicken crosswise. Divide rice,
chicken, and cucumbers between plates in separate sections. Top chicken with
remaining pan sauce and serve.

> Thinly slice pork crosswise.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.